<HEAD>With AM-Bush-NATO Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>President Pokes Fun At Himself</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush is a ``charismatic,
macho, visionary guy'' at least when it comes to braving the sea.
   Who says?
   George Bush.
   With tongue firmly in cheek.
   The president was asked at his news conference Monday if he
hadn't been risking life, limb and summit by riding the 6-foot
waves in a gale on Malta's Marsaxlokk Bay on a Navy launch.
   ``You've been to Maine,'' Bush told the reporter. ``Don't tell
me that little chop was risking anything. I haven't had that much
fun in a long time. Winds were up to 60 mph, 50 knots, which is a
big wind.''
   At his vacation home in Kennebunkport, Bush relaxes by driving
his 28-foot Cigarette boat into ocean waves, the power boater's
equivalent of riding a bucking bronco.
   ``Hot dogging?'' the president said. ``No. You know these
charismatic, macho, visionary guys. They'll do anything.''
