<FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Kohl     12-04 0307</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Kohl,0316</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kohl Aide Says East German Party `Incapable of Acting'</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-East Germany Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>TERRENCE PETTY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chancellor Helmut Kohl's chief aide
said Monday the crippled East German Communist Party is unable to
act and has lost its support.
   The aide, Rudolf Seiters, has been negotiating with with East
German leaders about financial aid, in exchange for which West
Germany wants assurances of free elections and economic reform.
   He also has been laying the groundwork for a Kohl visit to East
Germany this month, but no date has been set.
   Seiters told the Norddeutscher Rundfunk radio he assumes he will
return to East Germany this week to resume his talks, despite the
resignation of the ruling party Politburo and Central Committee.
   The party is ``now incapable of action, in a deep crisis'' and
has ``lost the trust of its supporters, its members and the people
in the German Democratic Republic,'' he said.
   West Germany has a ``responsibility to help in humanitarian
areas ... regardless of the events'' in the Communist Party, he
added.
   In East Germany, Seiters said, he probably will meet with
Premier Hans Modrow, a reformer who is emerging as the country's
main political figure. The Kohl aide indicated he also might speak
with members of Modrow's Cabinet, which includes some
non-Communists.
   West Germany has proposed establishing a hard-currency fund for
East Germans who use their new travel freedom to visit the West.
East Germany's currency is non-convertible, making it difficult for
East Germans to buy goods in the West.
   So far, East Germany has not been willing to meet Bonn's demand
that, in exchange, it stop requiring West Germans to pay 25 marks
($13) each time they enter East Germany.
   West Germany also wants the East German government to contribute
substantially to the proposed fund.
</TEXT>
