<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Peru-Crash     12-04 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Peru-Crash,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Crash Kills 19, Including 8 Members of Soccer Team</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight members of a soccer team, a club
official and 10 fans were killed when their truck careened off a
road in the desert 225 miles southeast of Lima, police said Monday.
   The accident occurred Sunday night when the truck's brakes
failed, according to the police report. The other 21 people aboard
the vehicle, all of them players or fans, were injured, including
several seriously.
   The players belonged a soccer team from a local agricultural
cooperative that had defeated a rival team in nearby Nazca, a town
renown for strangely designed lines in the desert that include huge
drawings of birds.
   The team and fans were returning home when the accident
occurred, police said.
