<HEAD>Travel: Road Atlas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Idyllwild, Calif., made it.
   So did East Lynne, Mo. (population 286).
   And Voorhees, N.J.
   They are among small U.S. towns now on the map. Or at least on
the maps in the 1990 edition of the Rand McNally Road Atlas.
   The new listings are among more than 19,000 changes in the
revised edition, according to Michael Dobson, Rand McNally vice
president of cartographic services.
   The others: Big River, Desert Shores, Hercules, Mad River,
Salton Sea Beach, Calif.; Oak Run, Ill.; Twin Lakes, Ohio; Plain
Grove, Pa.; Alton, Bayou Vista, Bayview, Beach City,
Bruceville-Eddy, Buckingham, Gholson, Hallsburg, Jamaica Beach,
Lucas, Meadows, Nassau Bay, Northlake, Old River-Winfree, Pleak,
and St. Hedwig, all in Texas.
