<HEAD>London Shares End Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shares finished lower on London's Stock Exchange
Monday, although bargain-hunting helped lift them from their lows
of the session.
   By the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was down 7.7 points, or 0.3 percent, at 2,303.4.
   The Financial Times 30-share index was down 10.6 points at
1,819.1 at the close. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 2.79
points to close at 1,254.20.
   Volume came to 484.4 million shares, down from 544.3 million
shares Friday.
</TEXT>
