Department that orders to U.S. factories for manufactured goods
fell 0.2 percent in October to their lowest level since July.
   The report was the latest indicator showing the economy slowing
as the year draws to an end. The manufacturing sector has been
particularly weak, prompting concern of possible layoffs and a rise
in the unemployment rate.
   The Commerce Department also said sales of new homes edged down
0.5 percent in October, the sixth monthly decline of the year but a
major improvement over September.
   The NYSE's composite index was up 0.31 at 193.97.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index had
fallen 0.98 to 374.60.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, IBM was up 2[ at 99\,
Chevron had gained } at 71[ and USX had jumped 2\ to 37 amid
continued takeover speculation involving corporate raider Carl
