<DOCNO> AP891204-0262 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-04-89 1622EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-SmithKlineBeecham     12-04 0284</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-SmithKline Beecham,0295</SECOND>
<HEAD>Merged Company Announces 12 Percent Pre-tax Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pharmaceuticals giant SmithKline Beecham PLC,
reporting its first results since a merger earlier this year, said
Monday that its nine-month pre-tax profit rose 12 percent.
   The company did not provide net profit and earnings per share.
It also did not specify third-quarter results. SmithKline said the
statement was a ``progress report'' rather than a full earnings
announcement.
   Britain's Beecham Group PLC and Philadelphia-based SmithKline
Beckman Corp. merged in July through an exchange of shares,
creating the world's second-largest pharmaceuticals company after
Rahway, N.J.-based Merck and Co. SmithKline Beecham said its
pre-tax profit for the nine months ended Sept. 30 came to 587.3
million pounds, or the equivalent $920 million, compared with 524.3
million pounds, or $822 million, in the same period a year ago.
   Nine-month trading profit rose 15.9 percent to 626.5 million
pounds from 540.6 million pounds, the company said.
   Sales from continuing operations rose 18 percent to 3.2 billion
pounds from 2.7 billion pounds. Sales were boosted by a 19 percent
increase in U.S. sales of the anti-ulcer drug Tagamet, the company
said.
   The company used a rate of exchange of $1.5672 per British
pound, the rate at the start of trading in London on Monday. The
company consolidated the pre-merger earnings for comparison
purposes.
   ``The quality of our trading performance during this first
reporting period of the new company provides a strong foundation
upon which we can build,'' company chairman Henry Wendt said in a
statement.
   SmithKline Beecham's next official results, for the full year
ending Dec. 31, aren't due until March. British companies
traditionally report earnings twice a year, while American
companies issue reports quarterly.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
