<HEAD>Leasing Company Orders Four Boeing Jets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Intercredit Corp., an aircraft leasing company
based in Atlanta, has ordered four Boeing 737 airliners, Boeing Co.
said Monday.
   The order is valued at about $125 million.
   Boeing has 2,727 orders for the 737 jet, which is made in
several variations. The specific model and engine type for the
Intercredit order are to be determined later.
